<subSubSection id="C326F2CAFFDBCA7BFF3D13FAFDC4F99A" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B83A141FFDBCA7BFF3D13FAFAECFBDA" blockId="18.[151,1436,972,1608]" box="[151,1400,1007,1032]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFF3D13FAFDFFFBDA" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Sigit" authorityYear="1992" box="[151,619,1008,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parahiyangum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFF3D13FAFE95FBDA" box="[151,257,1008,1032]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Simulium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFEBB13FAFE23FBDA" box="[273,439,1008,1032]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Gomphostilbia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFE6213FAFDFFFBDA" box="[456,619,1008,1032]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">parahiyangum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (not sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFADDCB0FFDBCA7BFD5913E5FC60FBDA" box="[755,1012,1007,1032]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref67574" refString="Takaoka, H. &amp; Sigit, S. H. (1992) A new blackfly species of Simulium (Gomphostilbia) from Java, Indonesia (Diptera: Simuliidae). Japanese Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 20, 135 - 142. https: // doi. org / 10.2149 / tmh 1973.20.135" type="journal article">Takaoka &amp; Sigit, 1992</bibRefCitation>
: Takaoka &amp; Davies, 1995: 50–51.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A141FFDBCA7BFF3D141EFF74FB82" blockId="18.[151,1436,972,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFF3D141EFD13FBFF" authority="Takaoka" authorityName="Takaoka" box="[151,647,1044,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sazalyi" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFF3D141EFE95FBFE" box="[151,257,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Simulium</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFEBE141EFE2EFBFE" box="[276,442,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Gomphostilbia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFE64141EFD88FBFE" box="[462,540,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sazalyi</emphasis>
Takaoka
</taxonomicName>
, Ya’cob &amp; Low, in Takaoka 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC71141FFB84FBFE" box="[987,1040,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al</emphasis>
., 2018a: (Female, male, pupa and larva).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A141FFDBCA7BFF6D1456FB12FAFA" blockId="18.[151,1436,972,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
This new species was first recorded from Peninsular Malaysia as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFC7E1456FA08FBA7" authority="Takaoka &amp; Sigit" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Sigit" authorityYear="1992" box="[980,1436,1116,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parahiyangum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC7E1456FC76FBA1" box="[980,994,1116,1139]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC541456FB9BFBA1" box="[1022,1039,1116,1139]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFB861456FB5BFBA6" box="[1068,1231,1116,1140]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">parahiyangum</emphasis>
Takaoka &amp; Sigit
</taxonomicName>
originally described from Java (
<bibRefCitation id="EFADDCB0FFDBCA7BFDAD1475FCB1FB4A" box="[519,805,1151,1176]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refId="ref67574" refString="Takaoka, H. &amp; Sigit, S. H. (1992) A new blackfly species of Simulium (Gomphostilbia) from Java, Indonesia (Diptera: Simuliidae). Japanese Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 20, 135 - 142. https: // doi. org / 10.2149 / tmh 1973.20.135" type="journal article">Takaoka and Sigit, 1992</bibRefCitation>
), based on the female, pupa and larvae collected from Gombak, Fraser’s Hill and elsewhere (Takaoka and Davies, 1995). Takaoka 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC4414AFFBB2FB6E" box="[1006,1062,1188,1212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
(2018a) described this species as a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFE9414C2FE4EFB32" box="[318,474,1224,1248]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sazalyi" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFE9414C2FED8FB0D" box="[318,332,1224,1247]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFECE14C2FEE1FB0D" box="[356,373,1224,1247]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFE2614C2FE4EFB32" box="[396,474,1224,1248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">sazalyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the smaller number of male upper-eye facets in 12–14 vertical columns and 13–15 horizontal rows (17 vertical columns and 15 horizontal rows in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFC7214E6FB45FAD6" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Sigit" authorityYear="1992" box="[984,1233,1260,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parahiyangum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC7214E6FC72FAD1" box="[984,998,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFBA814E6FB87FAD1" box="[1026,1043,1260,1283]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFB8414E6FB45FAD6" box="[1070,1233,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">parahiyangum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and pupal frons sparsely covered with tubercles (densely covered with tubercles in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFC2F151AFBE2FAFA" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Sigit" authorityYear="1992" box="[901,1142,1296,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parahiyangum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC2F151AFC07FAF5" box="[901,915,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC00151AFC2FFAF5" box="[938,955,1296,1319]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFC79151AFBE2FAFA" box="[979,1142,1296,1320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">parahiyangum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A141FFDBCA7BFF6D153EFEBCF9D2" blockId="18.[151,1436,972,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFE46153EFD2AFA9E" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Davies" authorityYear="1995" box="[492,702,1332,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentistylum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFE46153EFE6EFA99" box="[492,506,1332,1355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFDB9153EFDB0FA99" box="[531,548,1332,1355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFD97153EFD2AFA9E" box="[573,702,1332,1356]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">dentistylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the flat ventral plate in the male, gill with eight short filaments, and antennal sheath with tubercles in the pupa, and deep postgenal cleft and deep constriction between abdominal segments 4 and 
<quantity id="4CC40CA4FFDBCA7BFE6C1576FE65FA47" box="[454,497,1404,1429]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
the larva. However, it is distinguished from the latter species by the style lacking an apical spine in the male, antennal sheath with nine ridges with tubercles (ten ridges with tubercles in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFAFB15AAFE8CFA0E" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Davies" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentistylum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFAFB15AAFACBFA65" box="[1361,1375,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFAD115AAFA18FA65" box="[1403,1420,1440,1463]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFF3D15CEFE8CFA0E" box="[151,280,1476,1500]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">dentistylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and dorsal protuberances on abdominal segments 1–5 (such protuberances are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3CDAC2FFDBCA7BFAFA15CEFE8CF9D2" authorityName="Takaoka &amp; Davies" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Simuliidae" genus="Simulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentistylum" subGenus="Gomphostilbia">
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFAFA15CEFACAFA09" box="[1360,1374,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">S</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFAD115CEFA18FA09" box="[1403,1420,1476,1499]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">G</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B9487D53FFDBCA7BFF3D15E2FE8CF9D2" box="[151,280,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">dentistylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83A141FFDBCA7BFF6D1606FDC4F99A" blockId="18.[151,1436,972,1608]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">The pupae and larvae of this species are found in small to medium streams at low to medium elevations in many localities in Peninsular Malaysia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
